{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"86a42714-fc03-49c8-b42e-9b157dc54b49","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2 / .NET 9**, which supports the modern patterns. Here's the recommended approach:\n\n- **`TestContext`** — inject via **constructor** (not the legacy property setter)\n- **Sync init** — use the constructor\n- **Async init** — use `[TestInitialize]` returning `Task`\n\nExample:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private MyService _service;\n\n    // Constructor: sync init + TestContext injection\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        _service = new MyService();\n    }\n\n    // Async init runs before each test\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task InitAsync()\n    {\n        await _service.ConnectAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void SomeTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test\");\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_service);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- Constructor runs first (sync), then `[TestInitialize]` (async-capable).\n- Constructor-injected `TestContext` replaced the old `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` pattern in MSTest v3.\n- `[TestCleanup]` also supports `async Task` for teardown.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8be3b91a-b9d4-49ef-a1bd-b47ad172934f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In MSTest v3, the recommended approach has evolved:\n\n1. **TestContext injection**: In MSTest 3.x, `TestContext` can be injected via constructor (preferred) rather than the old property-based approach.\n\n2. **Initialization**: \n   - `[TestInitialize]` for synchronous init (can also be async - returns `Task`)\n   - `[TestInitialize]` supports `async Task` return type in MSTest v3\n   - Constructor for basic synchronous setup\n   - `IAsyncInitialization` is not a built-in MSTest thing\n   - `[ClassInitialize]` and `[ClassCleanup]` handle class-level setup and teardown\n   - You can combine constructor injection with `[TestInitialize]` methods that return `Task` for async operations\n\nLet me put together a straightforward example.","outputTokens":674,"requestId":"105A:34A53A:2E504F5:335E42A:6A02ED02"},"id":"f4fdf297-5596-41dc-8022-b714265eae09","timestamp":"2026-05-12T09:04:18.583Z","parentId":"495b6e70-e746-42c4-af2b-c4052bde12ad"}
